Israel â€™s TA-25 Index dropped 1.5
percent to 1,201.38 at 1:11 p.m. in  Tel Aviv , the lowest
intraday level since Sept. 20.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.   Avner Oil Exploration-LP (AVNRL IT) slid to the lowest
this month, declining 2.8 percent to 2.053 shekels. Israel
Electric Corp. suspended talks to buy natural gas from companies
invested in the Tamar drilling site, TheMarker reported, without
saying where it got the information. Delek Drilling-LP, another
partner in Tamar, retreated 3.2 percent to 11.52 shekels.  Ness Technologies Inc. (NSTC)   jumped 10 percent to 24.15
shekels, the highest since May 2010. The information technology-
services company agreed to be acquired by Citi Venture Capital
International for $7.75 (26.41 shekels) a share in cash.  Space Communication Ltd. (SCC)   gained the most since May
26, rising 3 percent to 62 shekels. The marketer of satellite
communication services won a five-year contract in  Africa  to
provide telecommunication services on its Amos 5 satellite.  To contact the reporter on this story:
